CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 7, 1953, pg. 27, reads: "Seek City Title - Westinghouse High School's crack basketball team will be seeking its fourth city cage championship in a row at the Pitt Field House Friday night against Langley. The Bulldogs are currently riding the crest of a 13-game win streak and will be favored to defend their title. Members of the team are, left to right, back row, Walden, Saunders, Phillips and Nunlist.  Front row: Coach Willard Fisher, McClellm [McClelland], Wilkerson (no longer with the team), Darkins and Kramer."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Westinghouse High School basketball team with coach Willard Fisher drawing diagram on floor, and front row from left: James McClelland, Wilkerson, "Stretch" Darkins or Dawkins, and Kramer; back row: Robert "Bobby" Walden, Saunders, Allison Phillips, and Nunlist
